much%20anyone%20to%20hear%2C%20but%20it's%20maybe%20especially%20hard%20for%20CEOs%20accustomed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-pause-some-big-decisions-economy-trade-tariffs-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalling%20the%20shots%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20getting%20kid-glove%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20when%20the%20top%20dog's%20transgression%20appears%20serious%20enough%2C%20some%20companies%20will%20tear%20up%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-amazon-job-cuts-corporate-lingo-layoffs-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elists%20of%20euphemisms%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20say%20it%20more%20or%20less%20plainly%3A%20We%20canned%20the%20big%20boss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20what%20happened%20Thursday%20at%20Kohl's.%20The%20retailer%20said%20it%20had%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkohls-ceo-fired-ashley-buchanan-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bterminate%26quot%3B%20Ashley%20Buchanan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who'd%20only%20been%20in%20the%20top%20spot%20for%20a%20few%20months%2C%20%26quot%3Bfor%20cause.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKohl's%20said%20in%20a%20regulatory%20filing%20that%20Buchanan%20had%20directed%20the%20company%20to%20do%20business%20with%20a%20vendor%20started%20by%20a%20person%20with%20whom%20he%20had%20an%20undisclosed%20personal%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20terse%20phrasing%20in%20Kohl's%20announcement%20is%20a%20reminder%20that%20corporate%20boards%20%E2%80%94%20eager%20to%20maintain%20credibility%20%E2%80%94%20will%20sometimes%20forgo%20their%20word-mincing%20habits%2C%20at%20least%20for%20what%20they%20deem%20to%20be%20serious%20matters%2C%20corporate%20observers%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20embrace%20of%20tougher%20language%20around%20CEO%20firings%20is%20most%20on%20display%20when%20there's%20been%20a%20perceived%20ethical%20breach%20or%20malfeasance%2C%20Donald%20Hambrick%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20and%20organization%20at%20Pennsylvania%20State%20University%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBoards%20now%20are%20emphatic%20about%20such%20dismissals%2C%20and%20in%20a%20way%20that%20they%20weren't%20decades%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20reason%2C%20Hambrick%20said%2C%20is%20that%20boards%20stand%20to%20gain%20if%20they%20appear%20to%20be%20taking%20a%20no-nonsense%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20signal%20that%20they%20want%20to%20be%20scrupulous%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d70aecd8-7884-4f0b-aa46-fe15ae2ab91d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20time%20for%20'softer%20language'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENadya%20Malenko%2C%20a%20professor%20in%20the%20finance%20department%20at%20Boston%20College%2C%20told%20BI%20in%20an%20email%20that%20strong%20and%20direct%20language%20isn't%20unusual%20in%20cases%20where%20there's%20been%20a%20scandal%20or%20a%20clear%20violation%20of%20fiduciary%20duties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20different%2C%20she%20said%2C%20from%20situations%20where%20a%20CEO%20might%20not%20have%20been%20a%20good%20fit%20or%20had%20made%20strategic%20blunders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20board%20needs%20to%20signal%20that%20it%20holds%20misconduct%20accountable%2C%20and%20using%20softer%20language%20will%20not%20achieve%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Malenko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20it's%20also%20often%20worthwhile%20for%20directors%20to%20adopt%20a%20serious%20tone%20to%20tamp%20down%20speculation%20that%20there's%20some%20wider%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20Kohl's%2C%20Malenko%20said%2C%20the%20board%20might%20have%20decided%20it%20was%20better%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bcrystal%20clear%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20firing%20rather%20than%20let%20investors%20wonder%20whether%20there%20was%20something%20more%20serious%20afoot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20a%20rise%20in%20Kohl's%20stock%20following%20the%20news%20could%20have%20been%20a%20sign%20that%20investors%20weren't%20happy%20with%20Buchanan's%20short-lived%20efforts%20to%20turn%20around%20the%20company.%20Another%20possible%20reason%20for%20the%20gain%2C%20Malenko%20said%2C%20might%20have%20been%20that%20investors%20were%20pleased%20to%20see%20the%20board%20doing%20its%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGains%20on%20Thursday%20and%20Friday%20pushed%20Kohl's%20shares%20up%20nearly%2012%25%20following%20the%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20attempted%20to%20reach%20Buchanan%20for%20comment%20through%20what%20appeared%20to%20be%20his%20personal%20email%3B%20his%20LinkedIn%20account%20appears%20to%20be%20deleted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKohl's%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI%20on%20its%20choice%20of%20wording%20in%20announcing%20Buchanan's%20firing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222cefd58b-243f-4ecf-8e11-4dba52ba614c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERetaining%20confidence%20in%20the%20board%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKathy%20Gersch%2C%20chief%20commercial%20officer%20at%20the%20change-management%20firm%20Kotter%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20because%20Buchanan%20was%20so%20new%20in%20the%20role%2C%20the%20board%20likely%20wanted%20to%20show%20investors%20and%20others%20that%20it%20hadn't%20made%20a%20bad%20call%20in%20assessing%20his%20abilities%20and%2C%20rather%2C%20that%20Buchanan's%20ouster%20related%20to%20what%20the%20company%20deemed%20a%20conflict%20of%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20board%20needs%20to%20convey%20a%20sense%20of%20competence%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20its%20ability%20to%20hire%20a%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKohl's%20announced%20in%20November%20that%20Buchanan%2C%20who'd%20been%20running%20the%20retailer%20Michaels%20since%202020%2C%20would%20take%20over%20Kohl's%20in%20early%202025.%20In%20January%2C%20Kohl's%2C%20which%20is%20based%20near%20Milwaukee%2C%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkohls-sephora-stores-shopping-sales-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslumping%20sales%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20said%20it%20would%20close%20more%20than%20two%20dozen%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGersch%20said%20directors%20often%20seek%20a%20balance%20between%20not%20disparaging%20someone%20they're%20pushing%20out%20and%20maintaining%20the%20board's%20legitimacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20sort%20of%20a%20demand%20from%20the%20public%20and%20shareholders%20for%20greater%20degrees%20of%20transparency%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPenn%20State's%20Hambrick%20said%20that%20with%20serious%20matters%2C%20it's%20good%20when%20companies%20dispense%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fman-tiktoker-office-workers-stop-using-military-speak-psa-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecorporate%20speak%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20doing%20so%20signals%20that%20boards%20are%20concerned%20foremost%20about%20ethics%20and%20adhering%20to%20company%20values%20and%20societal%20norms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20approach%20helps%20a%20board%20maintain%20its%20reputation%20and%20that%20of%20a%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20they%20sniff%20out%20ethical%20misdeeds%2C%20no%20matter%20by%20whom%2C%20including%20the%20CEO%2C%20the%20person%20will%20be%20gone%2C%26quot%3B%20Hambrick%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkohls-ceo-firing-plain-wording-leadership-boards-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746438601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68150d7ec6ad288d147fe2f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkohls-ceo-firing-plain-wording-leadership-boards-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kohl's%20said%20it%20had%20fired%20its%20still-new%20CEO%20%26quot%3Bfor%20cause.%26quot%3B%20Boards%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20ditch%20corporate%20euphemisms%20when%20they%20believe%20an%20issue%20is%20serious.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkohls-ceo-firing-plain-wording-leadership-boards-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Reddit%20CEO%20Steve%20Huffman%20says%20the%20company%20used%20to%20be%20so%20idealistic%20that%20people%20were%20'not%20working%20very%20hard'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Steve%20Huffman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ad24086630eb10385c77af%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReddit's%20CEO%20Steve%20Huffman%20said%20at%20one%20point%20employees%20were%20not%20'working%20hard'.'%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FYuki%20Iwamura%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EReddit's%20CEO%20said%20he%20had%20to%20remind%20employees%20to%20work%20hard%20when%20he%20returned%20in%202015.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThere's%20a%20tendency%20in%20US%20tech%20to%20place%20idealism%20above%20hard%20work%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EReddit's%20success%20is%20partly%20due%20to%20users%20treating%20it%20as%20a%20search%20engine%20for%20their%20queries.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20is%20worth%20nearly%20%2421%20billion%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddits-stock-jumped-after-first-quarter-earnings-report-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elast%20week's%20megahit%20earnings%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Its%20CEO%20said%20success%20took%20two%20decades%2C%20a%20big%20leadership%20change%2C%20and%20reminding%20employees%20they%20have%20to%20work%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20episode%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BProf%20G%20Pod%26quot%3B%20podcast%20released%20on%20Sunday%2C%20Reddit's%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%2C%20Steve%20Huffman%2C%20talked%20about%20the%20platform's%20founding%20journey.%20He%20also%20answered%20a%20question%20about%20the%20biggest%20changes%20he%20made%20that%20had%20the%20most%20impact%20at%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20biggest%20change%20was%20using%20common%20sense%2C%20debating%20whether%20their%20product%20was%20actually%20good%2C%20and%20being%20willing%20to%20change%20things%20to%20get%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnother%20big%20change%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-user-growth-usa-q2-earnings-results-social-media-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReddit%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20we%20weren't%20running%20as%20a%20business.%20We%20were%20really%20idealistic%2C%20and%20I%20think%20in%20many%20ways%20the%20idealism%20has%20been%20very%20good%2C%20but%20we%20were%20also%20idealistic%20about%20not%20being%20a%20business%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20not%20a%20great%20way%20to%20run%20a%20sustainable%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Huffman%20said%20about%20growing%20the%20company%20after%20he%20returned%20as%20CEO%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWrapped%20up%20in%20some%20of%20that%20idealism%20was%20also%20like%2C%20not%20working%20very%20hard%2C%26quot%3B%20Huffman%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuffman%20recalled%20telling%20employees%3A%20%26quot%3BLook%2C%20we%20have%20to%20work%20really%2C%20really%20hard.%20We're%20in%20a%20competitive%20space.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20don't%20work%20really%20hard%20and%20work%20really%20smart%20and%20make%20this%20thing%20successful%20both%20from%20a%20user%20point%20of%20view%20and%20business%20point%20of%20view%2C%20then%20we%20don't%20get%20to%20do%20this%2C%20and%20we'll%20never%20achieve%20our%20mission.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuffman%20cofounded%20Reddit%20with%20his%20college%20roommate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-cofounder-expects-swift-shift-back-to-dei-hiring-practices-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlexis%20Ohanian%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202005%20and%20oversaw%20its%202006%20acquisition%20by%20Cond%C3%A9%20Nast.%20He%20left%20the%20company%20to%20cofound%20the%20travel%20website%20Hipmunk%20before%20returning%20to%20Reddit%20as%20its%20CEO%20in%202015.%20Huffman%20was%20tasked%20with%20turning%20the%20company%20around%20after%20it%20faced%20a%20slew%20of%20challenges%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-reddit-hired-engineers-after-revolt-ceo-steve-huffman-interview-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edifficulty%20recruiting%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20bad%20publicity%20because%20of%20controversial%20content%20on%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20went%20public%20in%20March%202024%20and%20rose%20as%20much%20as%2070%25%20on%20its%20first%20trading%20day.%20Since%20then%2C%20its%20stock%20is%20up%20147%25%20and%20is%20worth%20about%20%24113.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday's%20podcast%2C%20Huffman%20said%20the%20sense%20of%20%26quot%3Bidealism%26quot%3B%20Reddit%20faced%20in%20its%20early%20days%20is%20a%20problem%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20as%20a%20whole.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20Bay%20Area%20broadly%20is%20this%2C%20it's%20almost%20an%20entitlement%20of%2C%20'I%20work%20at%20these%20companies%20but%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20work%20very%20hard%20and%20I'm%20here%20for%20myself%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuffman%20added%20that%20tech%20employees%2C%20including%20Reddit%20engineers%2C%20had%20a%20tendency%20to%20take%20ideas%20from%20other%20successful%20companies.%20He%20said%20his%20engineers%20adopted%20Apple's%20philosophy%20of%20%26quot%3Bit's%20done%20when%20it's%20done%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20used%20the%20phrase%20when%20he%20asked%20for%20product%20timelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20then%20the%20version%20I%20get%20isn't%20this%20artisanal%20world-class%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20Huffman%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20late%20and%20shitty.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CEO%20said%20